## Common Questions

### **Q: What if I miss the voting phase?**
**A:** Votes are tallied automatically when the round ends. You can still vote right up to the last minute. But try not to wait—vote early so you don't miss the deadline!

### **Q: Can I change my votes?**
**A:** Yes! You can change your proposal votes anytime before the round closes. For representative voting, you can update your Gold/Silver/Bronze allocation.

### **Q: What if my proposal doesn't make the top 2?**
**A:** Only the top 2 proposals advance to the next round. But your comments and ideas may have influenced other proposals—that's how Fractals work! The best ideas rise to the top across all proposals.

### **Q: Can I see who voted for whom?**
**A:** No, voting is **anonymous**. You can't see other people's individual votes—only the final scores and results. (Full vote information is stored in the database)

### **Q: What if I'm a representative in Round 2—do I have to participate?**
**A:** You're expected to! Representatives carry the voice of their Circle forward. If you can't make it, let the organizer know ASAP.

### **Q: How are ties broken?**
**A:** If two proposals or candidates have the same score, the system uses a tiebreaker (e.g., who got more votes, or a random selection). The organizer will explain their specific tiebreaker rules.

### **Q: Can I go back and see old rounds?**
**A:** Yes! After the Fractal ends, you can view the history of all rounds, proposals, and voting. This creates a transparent record of the decision-making process.

### **Q: What if someone is rude or off-topic?**
**A:** Report it to the Fractal organizer. They can moderate or remove disruptive members. The fractal is also self-organising and disruptive members will unlikely go the a second round.

