## Accessibility & Technical

### **Supported Devices**
- ✅ Mobile (iOS/Android) – Telegram web app
- ✅ Desktop (Mac/Windows) – Telegram web app

### **Telegram Setup**
- You must have Telegram installed or use Telegram Web
- Automatic login via the "Fractal App" button in Telegram
- No separate password needed

---

## Before You Start

### **Pre-Fractal Checklist**
- [ ] Join the Telegram group invite
- [ ] Read the Fractal topic description

### **What to Expect Timewise**

**Quick Decision (20-30 minutes per round):**
- For fast feedback or smaller groups
- Example: Weekly team priorities

**Standard Decision (1-2 hours per round):**
- For team meetings or group decisions
- Example: Product feature prioritization

**Deep Deliberation (1-3 days per round):**
- For major organizational decisions
- Example: Company strategy or policy changes

The organizer sets the round duration at the start—you'll be told how long each round lasts.

---

## Privacy & Data

- **Your votes are private** – No one sees who you voted for
- **Your messages in the group are shared** with Circle members
- **Proposals and comments are visible** to your Circle only
- **Final results are visible** to all Fractal participants
- **Data is kept** until the organizer deletes the Fractal

---

## Getting Help

**During the Fractal:**
- Ask the **Fractal organizer** for help
- Message in your Circle chat if confused about a proposal
- Check this manual for how features work

**Technical Issues:**
- Refresh the web app page
- Re-open Telegram and tap Fractal App again
- Contact the organizer if problems persist

